  "prompt": "What is a list of superforecasters?",
  "response": "Superforecasters are individuals who have demonstrated an exceptional ability to predict future events with greater accuracy than the general public or typical experts. They often participate in projects or tournaments where their forecasting skills are tested and evaluated. Some of the most well-known superforecasters have been associated with Philip Tetlock\u2019s Good Judgment Project, which was part of the larger IARPA (Intelligence Advanced Research Projects Activity) forecasting competition.\n\nWhile specific names of superforecasters may not be publicly listed due to privacy concerns or the terms of their participation agreements, some notable figures associated with the concept include:\n\n1. Philip E. Tetlock - Also the leading researcher in the field of expert judgment and forecasting.\n2. Barbara Mellers - Co-leader of the Good Judgment Project.\n3. Warren Hatch - CEO of Good Judgment Inc.\n4. David McCullough - Well-known for his accurate geopolitical predictions.\n5. Bill Flaherty - Recognized for his precise forecasts on economic trends.\n\nGood Judgment Inc. often spotlights superforecasters from their ranks, but individual identities are usually highlighted in specific publications, interviews, or articles related to their successful forecasting records. If you are looking for more detailed profiles and case studies of superforecasters, reading Philip Tetlock\u2019s book \"Superforecasting: The Art and Science of Prediction\" can provide deeper insights into their methods and achievements.",
